{"cursor":"3455","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nA 'play from scrimmage' is the activity of the games of Canadian football and\nAmerican football during which one team tries to advance the ball, get a first\ndown, or to score, and the other team tries to stop them or take the ball away.\nOnce a play is over, and before the next play starts, the football is considered\ndead. A game of American football (or Canadian Football) consists of many (about\n120-150) such plays.\n","linknr":209,"url":"Play_from_scrimmage","recorded":1362482941,"links":14,"instances":["american_football","football","football","football","football"],"pdf":[],"categories":["American football terminology"],"headings":["Specifications","The play","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["down","gridiron_football"],["dead_ball","football"],["down","football"],["punt","football"],["kickoff","american_football"],["field_goal","football"]],"members":["kickoff","field_goal","down","dead_ball","punt"],"related":["Canadian_football","American_football","Down_(gridiron_football)","Dead_ball_(football)","Offensive_team","Down_(football)","Forward_pass","Forward_pass","Quarterback","Forward_pass","Huddle","Defensive_team","Football_formation","Football_snap","Quarterback","Football_down","Interception","Fumble","First_down","Touchdown","First_down","Punt_(football)","Kickoff_(American_football)","Field_goal_(football)","Glossary_of_American_football"]}